            {"title":"Variables & Data Types","content":"<p>PHP variables start with <code>$</code>. Types are dynamic: <code>int</code>, <code>float</code>, <code>string</code>, <code>bool</code>, <code>array</code>, <code>null</code>. Use <code>gettype()</code> to check types.</p>"},
            {"title":"PHP in HTML","content":"<pre style='background:#1e1e2f;color:#e2e8f0;padding:15px;border-radius:8px;'>&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n  &lt;h1&gt;&lt;?php echo \"Dynamic Title\"; ?&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;\n  &lt;p&gt;Today is &lt;?= date('Y-m-d') ?&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;</pre>"},
